# whoOS
Custom pygame-based OS for Raspberry Pi 3A+ A 
portable device for programming, connecting to 
devices, and working with radio frequencies. 
---
## Hardware
- Raspberry Pi 3A+ (512MB RAM, aarch64) - 
Waveshare 3.5" TFT 480x320 (ILI9486, /dev/fb1, 
SPI) - SSD1309 OLED 128x64 (I2C 0x3C) - DHT11 
on GPIO4 (3.3V) - ADS7846 touchscreen - HS6209 
2.4G wireless keyboard (/dev/input/event0, 
xinput id=7) - NRF24L01+PA+LNA (SPI1, 2.4GHz, 
up to 1km range) - W5500 Ethernet module (SPI) 
---
## Hardware Wiring
### Waveshare 3.5" LCD
Plugs directly onto GPIO header, occupies SPI0 
entirely. Driver: fb_ili9486, display: 
/dev/fb1, redirect: con2fbmap 1 1
### SSD1309 OLED
    VCC -> Pin 1 (3.3V) GND -> Pin 6 (GND) SDA 
    -> Pin 3 (GPIO2, SDA) SCL -> Pin 5 (GPIO3, 
    SCL)
### DHT11
    VCC -> Pin 1 (3.3V) GND -> Pin 6 (GND) DATA 
    -> Pin 7 (GPIO4)
### NRF24L01+PA+LNA (2.4GHz)
    GND -> Pin 34 (GND) V+ -> Pin 17 (3.3V) -- 
    3.3V ONLY, not 5V! CE -> Pin 37 (GPIO26) 
    CSN -> Pin 36 (GPIO16, SPI1 CE0) SCK -> Pin 
    40 (GPIO21, SPI1 SCLK) MOSI -> Pin 38 
    (GPIO20, SPI1 MOSI) MISO -> Pin 35 (GPIO19, 
    SPI1 MISO)
### W5500 Ethernet
    VCC -> Pin 2 (5V) GND -> Pin 25 (GND) CS -> 
    Pin 11 (GPIO17) SCK -> Pin 40 (GPIO21, SPI1 
    SCLK) MOSI -> Pin 38 (GPIO20, SPI1 MOSI) 
    MISO -> Pin 35 (GPIO19, SPI1 MISO) RST -> 
    Pin 31 (GPIO6)
---
## Autostart
    ~/.bash_profile -> startx -> ~/.xinitrc -> 
    python3 main.py X server runs via fbdev on 
    /dev/fb1 If HDMI is connected -> 
    auto-switches to HDMI with auto resolution 
    detection
---
## Project Structure
    whoOS/
